# Experience Portfolio Database Schema

## companies
- id: integer, primary key
- name: string
- location: string // city or "Remote"
- industry: string, optional
- employee_count: integer, optional // e.g., 50, 500
- website: string, optional
- logo_url: string, optional // for frontend display
- timestamps

## company_experiences
- id: integer, primary key
- company_id: integer, foreign key -> companies.id
- title: string // e.g., "Senior Software Engineer"
- joining_date: date
- leaving_date: date, nullable // null means current
- description: text // can store HTML or Markdown
- experience_letter: string // file attachment URL/path
- relieving_letter: string // file attachment URL/path
- timestamps

## skills
- id: integer, primary key
- name: string // e.g., "Ruby on Rails"
- slug: string, unique
- proficiency_level: string // enum: Beginner | Intermediate | Advanced
- years_of_experience: float // allow fractional (e.g., 2.5)
- timestamps

## experience_skills (join table)
- id: integer, primary key
- skill_id: integer, foreign key -> skills.id
- company_experience_id: integer, foreign key -> company_experiences.id
- notes: text, optional // e.g. "Used for backend APIs"
- timestamps

## client_projects
- id: integer, primary key
- name: string // project title
- company_experience_id: integer, foreign key -> company_experiences.id
- description: text
- tech_stack: string or json, optional // list of technologies used
- start_date: date, optional
- end_date: date, optional
- role: string // e.g., "Lead Developer"
- project_url: string, optional
- timestamps

## project_images
- id: integer, primary key
- client_project_id: integer, foreign key -> client_projects.id
- image_url: string
- caption: string, optional // alt text or description
- position: integer // for ordering
- timestamps

## client_reviews
- id: integer, primary key
- client_project_id: integer, foreign key -> client_projects.id
- client_name: string
- client_position: string // e.g., "CTO, Acme Inc."
- review_text: text
- rating: integer, optional // 1â€“5
- timestamps
